Blocks.Text: So he put up for the night at The Admiral's Head, that
famous Partmouth hostelny, second only in historic
interest to the George, unhappily destroyed by German
lombs during the last war. Having deposited his
laggage and unpacked his overnight bag he
went in search of a drink. The lower bar was
empty, save for the lady known by all habritue
man who was staring moodily into a gin
